# Tool Renderer Performance

Tool renderers live inside streaming chat messages. The AI SDK creates **new object references** for `part.output`, `part.input`, and `part.result` on every stream token — even when values haven't changed. Without proper memoization, every streaming token re-renders ALL tool components in the message (including completed ones), causing the UI to freeze or crash.

## Rules

### 1. Always wrap tool components in `memo()` with a custom comparator

Never rely on default shallow-reference comparison — object props from the AI SDK will always be new references.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — re-renders on every stream token
export const MyTool = ({ state, output, input }: Props) => { ... };

// ❌ STILL BAD — memo with default comparison fails on object props
export const MyTool = memo(({ state, output, input }: Props) => { ... });

// ✅ GOOD — custom comparator with value-based checks for objects
export const MyTool = memo(({ state, output, input }: Props) => {
  ...
}, (prev, next) => {
  return (
    prev.state === next.state &&
    prev.className === next.className &&
    shallowEqual(prev.output, next.output) &&
    shallowEqual(prev.input, next.input)
  );
});
MyTool.displayName = 'MyTool';
```

### 2. Use `shallowEqual` for object props, `===` for primitives

A `shallowEqual` helper exists in `tool.tsx`. For `result`-style objects with known fields, compare fields individually:

```tsx
// For known shapes (e.g., CodeExecutionResult):
prev.result.stdout === next.result.stdout &&
prev.result.stderr === next.result.stderr &&
prev.result.return_code === next.result.return_code

// For opaque objects (e.g., generic tool output/input):
shallowEqual(prev.output, next.output)
```

### 3. Debounce expensive operations during streaming

Shiki syntax highlighting (`codeToHtml`) is very expensive. Never run it on every streaming token.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — fires on every code change during streaming
useEffect(() => {
  highlightCode(code, language).then(setHtml);
}, [code]);

// ✅ GOOD — debounce + cancellation
useEffect(() => {
  let cancelled = false;
  const timer = setTimeout(() => {
    highlightCode(code, language).then(([light, dark]) => {
      if (!cancelled) { setHtml(light); setDarkHtml(dark); }
    });
  }, 150);
  return () => { cancelled = true; clearTimeout(timer); };
}, [code, language]);
```

### 4. Never create new arrays/objects in the render body

Move static arrays (like zoom levels) outside the component. Avoid inline object creation that defeats memoization.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — new array every render
function MyComponent() {
  const LEVELS = [0.5, 1, 1.5, 2];
  ...
}

// ✅ GOOD — stable reference
const LEVELS = [0.5, 1, 1.5, 2];
function MyComponent() { ... }
```
